content: It amazing, I also have the physical boardgame and I love it. You can play it alone, on different difficulties, with or without the expansion. The music and graphics are really lovely. I haven't experienced any errors yet and there are no adds. Totally recommend!

This is an easy but engaging game. It mixes matching strategy, set collection and a little luck. The board is beautiful. The AI has a challenging variety. The different powers that affect scoring in the expansion really makes each game different. This is a polished, well-produced digital version of a boardgames.

Desperately in need of an update. A beautiful and fun game but does not at all fit the screen of my phone (Pixel 4XL). Would look so much better and be much more playable if it did.
replyContent: Hello! Thank you so much for the feedback. I have passed this along to the team. Thank you for taking the time to reach out!

content: This app is an excellent implementation of a great game, and it includes the expansion, which makes the game even better. My only request is that I wish it had a back button for those times when I accidentally place a tile in an unintended location.
replyContent: Hi There! Thank you so much for your feedback! This has been passed along to the team so that they can take a look. Please feel free to reach out again with any further questions or feedback!

content: I'm enjoying the game so far but anything that requires a login is blocked to me - I try to register and it says I already have an account, I try to recover password and it says it's emailed me but then nothing happens.. :(
replyContent: Hi Laura! Thanks for taking the time to leave a review, we are so sorry to hear you are having trouble logging in! Would you mind dropping a line to support@direwolfdigital.com so we can take a look?

content: Beautiful, relaxing and fun.

content: Game is just like the board game, and it's easy to track and play with friends. Loses a star because if you leave the app and come back it always has to log you back in. This occasionally results in not connecting, which then requires you to fully close and then reopen the app. Again, the game itself is great and just like the board game, with pretty good graphics and audio.
Very nice adaptation of the game!
One of my favorites!p
Not sure why a game app needs access to "photos, media and files" on my device...
Nice graphics, terrific UI and decent AI.
A great board game made into an excellent app. I love the music, sounds and everything about this digital implementation. Whenever I need to relax, I play Lanterns and zen out.
Enjoyable
Amazingly good! Totally worth getting if you like the boardgame
Beautiful app version of this game. I would like to see more online players.
Awesome game

Really good implementation of the game and expansion, BUT: This heats my phone up and drains the batteries like no other. The graphics are good, but there isn't enough complexity to explain why this game is killing my phone. I have a Pixel XL 1st generation, which is a bit old, but it's plenty powerful to handle these kinds of graphics with ease. Maybe there's no frame timer in the inner loop, so the game is running at 100% CPU drawing frames that will never get displayed? Good game otherwise.
It is a great game. The app works well. I like that you can play multiplayer hot seat. I also appreciate that the expansion is included even though I prefere to play the basic game.
Great game
This is so fun. I'm addicted!

Pleasing casual game, very pretty to look at, has chill background music and sounds, works smoothly. Very nice casual game for your device, but also good for teaching beginners how to play the tabletop Lanterns game with others.
Fun just like the board game, except can play anytime with people.

I love the game. I usually play with my boyfriend. An annoying thing I noticed: I don't get notified the opponent finished and it's my turn. i have to ask him and then go back to "home" screen and continue from there at every turn. He doesn't experience this problem. I have a Google Nexus 5 phone.
Would be 5* if it had an undo button.
Login does not work half the time, why did they not just use the built in Google play account, big pain, tells me I am already logged in, then says my password is wrong, then works 5 mins later.

It's not a credit card account why would I need to log in every time, plus the log in is buggy keeps telling wrong username or password. There are bugs in the lantern exchange that won't  allow me to change my selection.  Long wait in rank query and weird friend invitations.
It took me a while to figure out how to rotate tiles. I have to manually shut down the app when I'm ready to leave, there's no option to leave it.

Takes a couple games to understand the rules, then a few more to appreciate the strategy. But once you get it, it's super fun. I love the fact that you can play friends or strangers for ranking online, and that it saves your stats in the cloud for access across devices. Highly recommended!

Okay so this game is ingenious and the physical version is perfect. This app is essentially the same except for a few annoying things, namely when a pile is out of cards you have to pause the game and gonto a different screen to see it which is highly unintuitive and there is a game losing bug where if you grab a tile with your finger and then decide to place it back in your hand and the game decides, "nope, you placed that. No backsies."

One of the best looking board game adaptions around. Loses a star for a simple pet peeve of mine - you can't mix multiple human and AI opponents. This game easily works best with 4 players, so it really needs the option to add AI opponents to a 2 or 3 player pass and play game

Close to being my all-time favorite android game pastime. Just an all-around excellent job all around, artwork, user interface look-and-feel, and mimicing the gameplay of the tabletop version. Kudos from a fellow software engineer. Five stars in all categories.
Lanterns is second only to Cosmic Encounter! Yes, I'm biased.

The game loads fast, doesn't appear to have any glitches that I've noticed, and the game has never shut down on me. I've been using this app for about a month now. I really liked the board game and this allows me to practice and see the differences in different number of players. Highly recommend.
Including the wide variety of ways to play (solo, pass/play, online ranked) and the thorough tutorial -  anyone can learn/love this game in 1 minute

It's just as enjoyable as the physical game itself. Wonderful colors and soundtrack. I was worried how they would do tile placement, but it's just fine and very intuitive.
